metadata.name: Screams out of my head.
metadata.description:
There she sits
With all those noises in her head
Years of pains and tears
Bottling everything within herself
She told herself no one will listen
She told herself she was at fault
She blamed herself for the pains inflicted on her
Her pillow drenched in tears every night
Her face filled with smile in the morning
All she ever wished for is to be able to scream out her pains
To be able to get them all out
Probably if she scream out of her head
She will feel so much better
And be able to have a peaceful sleep and dreams.
